description:
&lt;p&gt;A new opportunity has arisen for a SystmOne Developer to join our successful and established development team based within the IM&amp;T Directorate of Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be responsible for the full development lifecycle of assigned units including analysis, development, training and rollout. There will also be a requirement to develop existing SystmOne units. The role will also be responsible for the supervision of two junior SystmOne Developers; including management of work, support in the development of requests and troubleshooting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Clinical Applications Architect to develop timescales for all scheduled work, including new SystmOne units and the development of existing units.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively work with the EPR Development team to provide a consistent approach to unit builds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership for the delivery of all work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop SystmOne in a structured and methodical manner adhering to best practice and Trust standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage two SystmOne staff, to ensuring all develop and support commitments are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic candidate with excellent communication skills and a desire to deliver fast paced change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have development experience of SystmOne&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience of writing system specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have strong interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the healthcare sector, ideally community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
